<item>
            <title>[HBASE-7820] Authenticating users from different realm without a trust relationship</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7820</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;HBase servers are part of the Hadoop domain, controlled by Hadoop Active Directory. &lt;br/&gt;
The users belong to the CORP domain, controlled by the CORP Active Directory. &lt;br/&gt;
In the absence of a one way trust from HADOOP DOMAIN to CORP DOMAIN, how will HBase servers authenticate CORP users ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is the HBase equivalent of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-9296&quot; title=&quot;Authenticating users from different realm without a trust relationship&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-9296&quot;&gt;HADOOP-9296&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
