                            <comment id="13579649" author="apurtell" created="Sat, 16 Feb 2013 00:58:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I skimmed the &apos;multirealm.pdf&apos; attachment on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-9296&quot; title=&quot;Authenticating users from different realm without a trust relationship&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-9296&quot;&gt;HADOOP-9296&lt;/a&gt;. Be aware that every RegionServer authenticates users in an HBase cluster.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The code changes for 0.94 look ok as they mirror what is being done over in Hadoop RPC. Insure that HBase can compile against both versions of Hadoop 1 and Hadoop 2 in the 0.94 POM with the changes included.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, we will need a trunk patch because changes need to be committed to trunk before any branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
